1
00:00:23,541 --> 00:00:25,916
[EHYEH] Everything in this
world has spawned forth from

2
00:00:26,000 --> 00:00:28,500
the dreams of the goddess Eve.

3
00:00:28,583 --> 00:00:30,708
And we that live
in it, are merely visions

4
00:00:30,791 --> 00:00:33,791
the dreams source
has given life.

5
00:00:33,875 --> 00:00:38,375
Then, what does that make us?
Where are our true selves?

6
00:00:38,458 --> 00:00:41,416
I say unto you: those with
the Sleeping Beauty Syndrome

7
00:00:41,500 --> 00:00:44,666
are on the true path.
Why waste your time grieving?

8
00:00:44,750 --> 00:00:46,375
Those maidens are fortunate.

9
00:00:46,458 --> 00:00:49,333
The dream world has awakened
them to their true selves.

10
00:00:49,416 --> 00:00:52,125
They have received
Eve's blessing!

11
00:00:52,208 --> 00:00:54,958
Verily, unfettered by the
shackles of this world,

12
00:00:55,041 --> 00:00:58,000
they have blazed a
trail to true freedom!

13
00:00:58,083 --> 00:01:00,291
With the liberty to
behave like witches,

14
00:01:00,375 --> 00:01:02,416
they have redefined beauty!

15
00:01:02,500 --> 00:01:06,500
Eh? Is someone here actually
taking that loud fool seriously?

16
00:01:06,583 --> 00:01:07,875
[KANZAKI gasps]

17
00:01:15,750 --> 00:01:20,750
♪


18
00:02:49,000 --> 00:02:50,791
Great news! I found a clue!


19
00:02:50,875 --> 00:02:52,041
[HARUTO]
Huh?

20
00:02:52,125 --> 00:02:54,333
It might help get Yurina
out of the dream world.

21
00:02:54,416 --> 00:02:57,833
More importantly, why am I the
only one who can't wake up?

22
00:02:57,916 --> 00:02:59,083
[KANZAKI]
Huh?

23
00:02:59,166 --> 00:03:01,458
All the witches have
woken up, haven't they?

24
00:03:12,375 --> 00:03:13,791
I'm checking on that.

25
00:03:13,875 --> 00:03:15,958
But from what I can tell,
all of the girls suffering from

26
00:03:16,041 --> 00:03:18,666
Sleeping Beauty Syndrome have
returned to the real world.

27
00:03:18,750 --> 00:03:21,416
Well, with one exception,
it saddens me to say.

28
00:03:21,500 --> 00:03:23,166
An exception?

29
00:03:23,250 --> 00:03:27,416
One of the girls passed away.
The Witch of First Love.

30
00:03:27,500 --> 00:03:29,333
Kayo Sugisaki.

31
00:03:29,416 --> 00:03:31,083
Yeah, I remember.

32
00:03:39,125 --> 00:03:40,458
Still, when do I get out?

33
00:03:40,541 --> 00:03:42,541
That's why I tried to tell
you about the Yurina clue.

34
00:03:42,625 --> 00:03:44,875
It might be the key to solving
the mystery about you.

35
00:03:44,958 --> 00:03:47,666
And, not just you,
but Lily as well!

36
00:03:47,750 --> 00:03:49,541
I don't care about
any of this stuff!

37
00:03:49,625 --> 00:03:50,916
This could all be tied to you!

38
00:03:51,000 --> 00:03:52,708
What do you mean you don't care?

39
00:03:52,791 --> 00:03:55,750
I suspect that everything
is interconnected!

40
00:03:55,833 --> 00:03:59,000
[HARUTO] I suspect that all you
really care about is yourself!

41
00:03:59,083 --> 00:04:00,583
As long as you can
save your sister,

42
00:04:00,666 --> 00:04:03,208
you don't give a damn about
what happens to me, right?

43
00:04:03,291 --> 00:04:04,625
[KANZAKI]
How dare you.

44
00:04:04,708 --> 00:04:06,583
You should apologize
for what you just said.

45
00:04:06,666 --> 00:04:07,791
[HARUTO]
Not happening.

46
00:04:07,875 --> 00:04:09,833
I want some answers,
and I want them now!

47
00:04:09,916 --> 00:04:14,083
[KANZAKI sighs] At the very
least, I'm more mature than you.

48
00:04:14,166 --> 00:04:15,875
[HARUTO]
Yeah? So what?

49
00:04:15,958 --> 00:04:17,666
I have come to the conclusion
that this back and forth

50
00:04:17,750 --> 00:04:19,791
is unproductive, therefore,
there is no further reason

51
00:04:19,875 --> 00:04:22,500
to continue our discourse.

52
00:04:22,583 --> 00:04:24,416
Are you heading out to
look for your sister?

53
00:04:24,500 --> 00:04:27,666
You said something about a
clue earlier, didn't you?

54
00:04:27,750 --> 00:04:28,916
What's wrong?

55
00:04:29,000 --> 00:04:31,166
[KANZAKI] I don't feel
like talking anymore.

56
00:04:32,833 --> 00:04:34,333
Hold on!

57
00:04:38,041 --> 00:04:41,583
[HARUTO gasps]
I want this dream to end!

58
00:05:15,708 --> 00:05:17,875
I represent the
Thorn Cross Association.

59
00:05:17,958 --> 00:05:20,291
I'm Ehyeh. Nice to meet you.

60
00:05:20,375 --> 00:05:23,708
Professor Kanzaki. Your research
in the dream world is easily

61
00:05:23,791 --> 00:05:27,041
the finest work done
in the field to date.

62
00:05:27,125 --> 00:05:30,000
It's an honor to meet
you in the flesh.

63
00:05:30,083 --> 00:05:32,041
[HARUTO]
Hm?

64
00:05:32,125 --> 00:05:33,791
Hey, Brother!

65
00:05:33,875 --> 00:05:35,041
Oh, it's you.

66
00:05:35,125 --> 00:05:37,291
So you and the professor
got into a fight, huh?

67
00:05:37,375 --> 00:05:38,916
How do you know about that?

68
00:05:39,000 --> 00:05:40,583
Because it's all a dream!

69
00:05:40,666 --> 00:05:42,666
I'm ready for this dream to end.

70
00:05:42,750 --> 00:05:44,458
Would you like to know
why you're the only one

71
00:05:44,541 --> 00:05:46,583
who still hasn't woken up yet?

72
00:05:46,666 --> 00:05:49,500
What? Do you know why
I'm still dreaming?

73
00:05:49,583 --> 00:05:52,208
I can tell you exactly why
you're still in slumber.

74
00:05:52,291 --> 00:05:54,375
It's because I'm the
one keeping you asleep!

75
00:05:54,458 --> 00:05:57,166
[HARUTO gasps]

76
00:05:57,250 --> 00:06:00,291
Oh? You really surprise me,
Professor Kanzaki.

77
00:06:00,375 --> 00:06:02,416
You aren't familiar with Eve?

78
00:06:02,500 --> 00:06:04,458
No, I'm afraid not.

79
00:06:04,541 --> 00:06:07,208
Actually, my younger sister
has Sleeping Beauty Syndrome,

80
00:06:07,291 --> 00:06:09,375
and I was wondering whether
her case and the others were

81
00:06:09,458 --> 00:06:10,833
related by a common source.

82
00:06:10,916 --> 00:06:13,583
That's wonderful! Rejoice,
for your sister receives

83
00:06:13,666 --> 00:06:15,291
the blessings of Eve
in the dream world,

84
00:06:15,375 --> 00:06:17,291
like a flower
blooms in the sun!

85
00:06:17,375 --> 00:06:19,375
[KANZAKI grunts]

86
00:06:19,458 --> 00:06:22,500
'Kay, so, what exactly is
it that you want from me?

87
00:06:22,583 --> 00:06:24,833
Something important
that only you can do.

88
00:06:24,916 --> 00:06:27,291
Because, I've come to believe
that you and you alone have

89
00:06:27,375 --> 00:06:29,875
what it takes to prevent
Eve from ever reawakening.

90
00:06:29,958 --> 00:06:31,875
Eve, who? What're
you talking about?

91
00:06:31,958 --> 00:06:35,291
Eve is Eve. You know,
as in "Adam and Eve".

92
00:06:42,208 --> 00:06:43,958
[LILY]
If Eve awakens...

93
00:06:48,458 --> 00:06:50,333
[LILY]
...then everyone will die.

94
00:06:59,416 --> 00:07:02,666
Her promise will provide
salvation for all of humanity.

95
00:07:02,750 --> 00:07:04,833
[KANZAKI grunts]

96
00:07:04,916 --> 00:07:07,000
[EHYEH] This is what we in the
Thorn Cross Association

97
00:07:07,083 --> 00:07:09,541
firmly believe, and so we
worship the goddess Eve,

98
00:07:09,625 --> 00:07:12,041
who sleeps in the center
of the dream world.

99
00:07:12,125 --> 00:07:14,458
A mighty being responsible
for not only the beginning

100
00:07:14,541 --> 00:07:17,375
of this world, but also
the birth of mankind.

101
00:07:17,458 --> 00:07:18,875
[KANZAKI] Back out on
the street, you said that

102
00:07:18,958 --> 00:07:20,875
the entire world is no
more than a dream that

103
00:07:20,958 --> 00:07:24,166
Eve is having, right? I still
don't understand that aspect.

104
00:07:24,250 --> 00:07:27,041
[EHYEH] You're already familiar
with the story of Adam and Eve,

105
00:07:27,125 --> 00:07:30,125
I presume. They were the
first man and first woman,

106
00:07:30,208 --> 00:07:33,083
blessed by God with
the Garden of Eden.

107
00:07:33,166 --> 00:07:36,208
However, they were tricked by
the devil into consuming fruit

108
00:07:36,291 --> 00:07:39,000
from the Tree of Knowledge,
which angered God,

109
00:07:39,083 --> 00:07:40,833
and he threw
them out of Eden.

110
00:07:40,916 --> 00:07:42,750
[KANZAKI]
Yes, I've heard that much.

111
00:07:42,833 --> 00:07:45,166
[EHYEH] After lamenting
her actions for years,

112
00:07:45,250 --> 00:07:48,041
Eve was so tormented by what
she'd done that she closed

113
00:07:48,125 --> 00:07:50,291
off her heart from
the rest of the world,

114
00:07:50,375 --> 00:07:52,833
and fell into a deep slumber.

115
00:07:52,916 --> 00:07:55,458
In her sleep, she would
give birth to dreams.

116
00:07:55,541 --> 00:07:58,500
In turn forming this
world in which we live.

117
00:07:58,583 --> 00:08:00,583
If we take a look
through history, it becomes

118
00:08:00,666 --> 00:08:04,125
clear that our reality is far
from the paradise of Eden.

119
00:08:04,208 --> 00:08:07,000
People suffer from one
illness or calamity to another,

120
00:08:07,083 --> 00:08:09,625
the gap between rich
and poor grows wider,

121
00:08:09,708 --> 00:08:12,250
and war is waged
with no end in sight.

122
00:08:12,333 --> 00:08:15,125
Man continues to
grow more depraved.

123
00:08:15,208 --> 00:08:17,416
All because we ate from
the Tree of Knowledge.

124
00:08:17,500 --> 00:08:20,541
God was furious at
man's transgression.

125
00:08:20,625 --> 00:08:22,666
Now we receive his punishment.

126
00:08:22,750 --> 00:08:26,583
That is the core of Eve's dream,
and it is what we call reality.

127
00:08:26,666 --> 00:08:28,666
The here and now.

128
00:08:28,750 --> 00:08:31,416
Then, if this is all a dream,
what does that make us?

129
00:08:31,500 --> 00:08:34,000
Our forms are naught
but temporary illusions.

130
00:08:34,083 --> 00:08:36,458
True reality lives
inside dreams.

131
00:08:36,541 --> 00:08:40,333
[KANZAKI] You mean,
that's my truest aspect?

132
00:08:40,416 --> 00:08:43,333
We must all endeavor to
awaken to our dream selves.

133
00:08:43,416 --> 00:08:46,000
For only then will
we find salvation.

134
00:08:46,083 --> 00:08:48,750
The key to such self-discovery
lies in the witches who built

135
00:08:48,833 --> 00:08:50,833
kingdoms in the dream world.

136
00:08:50,916 --> 00:08:52,416
The witches?

137
00:08:52,500 --> 00:08:55,708
Eve found respite in slumber,
and her dreams helped to shape

138
00:08:55,791 --> 00:08:57,708
this world of suffering.

139
00:08:57,791 --> 00:08:59,666
But what about the
maidens with what we call

140
00:08:59,750 --> 00:09:02,291
"Sleeping Beauty Syndrome?"

141
00:09:02,375 --> 00:09:06,791
Yea, they construced a dream
world of only witches.

142
00:09:06,875 --> 00:09:07,958
In that world of theirs,

143
00:09:08,041 --> 00:09:10,250
everything they
desired became real.

144
00:09:10,333 --> 00:09:15,375
Such a wonderful place.
It is the true Garden of Eden!

145
00:09:27,833 --> 00:09:30,500
[EHYEH] And at the moment that
Eve reawakens, mankind will

146
00:09:30,583 --> 00:09:33,958
finally be set free from this
world of suffering she's made.

147
00:09:34,041 --> 00:09:35,583
No more war or poverty.

148
00:09:35,666 --> 00:09:38,750
No. Nothing short of
an eternal paradise.

149
00:09:38,833 --> 00:09:40,708
[KANZAKI] So then, what you're
saying is the witches should

150
00:09:40,791 --> 00:09:42,208
never be woken up?

151
00:09:42,291 --> 00:09:44,166
Because they've developed
into their true selves,

152
00:09:44,250 --> 00:09:46,333
and set an example
for the rest of us?

153
00:09:46,416 --> 00:09:49,458
Precisely. And yet, someone
dares keep them from their

154
00:09:49,541 --> 00:09:52,458
true selves. Returning them
to this world of pain.

155
00:09:52,541 --> 00:09:53,500
[gasps]

156
00:09:53,583 --> 00:09:56,000
[EHYEH]
Someone evil to their core.

157
00:10:00,791 --> 00:10:02,375
 All of the witches
you've saved thus far

158
00:10:02,458 --> 00:10:03,875
have been vital to my plan.

159
00:10:03,958 --> 00:10:06,291
They're the linchpins whose
existence grant us access to

160
00:10:06,375 --> 00:10:08,333
Eve's door, which we'll
need to open.

161
00:10:08,416 --> 00:10:10,916
The witches?
They're all connected?

162
00:10:11,000 --> 00:10:14,125
[LILY]
Yes. Remember?

163
00:10:14,208 --> 00:10:17,250
Game set and match.
Ah, I feel better.

164
00:10:17,333 --> 00:10:20,625
Who's the mightiest witch in
the whole world, my darlings?

165
00:10:20,708 --> 00:10:23,125
[STUFFED ANIMALS]
The Witch of Thunder is!

166
00:10:23,208 --> 00:10:25,291
[HARUTO] This is a pathetic
"dream world", if you ask me.

167
00:10:25,375 --> 00:10:27,166
The whole thing seems
kind of thrown together.

168
00:10:27,250 --> 00:10:29,583
[THE WITCH OF THUNDER] You don't
know how tiring it is to be the

169
00:10:29,666 --> 00:10:32,500
girl everyone expects me
to be. I'm not allowed to fail!

170
00:10:32,583 --> 00:10:34,250
It's too much pressure.

171
00:10:34,333 --> 00:10:38,125
I really want to be spoiled.
To have my way, but I can't!

172
00:10:38,208 --> 00:10:40,916
That's why I felt like there was
no choice but to bind myself.

173
00:10:41,000 --> 00:10:42,666
At least I have some
control in this world.

174
00:10:42,750 --> 00:10:45,041
I can do what I
want when I like!

175
00:10:48,291 --> 00:10:51,625
I've dreamed about
this for a long time.

176
00:10:51,708 --> 00:10:54,250
[HARUTO] The dream of yours,
it's over once you've killed

177
00:10:54,333 --> 00:10:58,666
all three of them. It will end.
What will you do then?

178
00:10:58,750 --> 00:11:02,666
\What I do after doesn't matter.
If they don't die, I can't live.

179
00:11:02,750 --> 00:11:08,791
[KAYO] Why is it
always me? It isn't fair!

180
00:11:08,875 --> 00:11:11,583
[WITCH OF GLUTTONY] When I eat,
I put on weight really fast.

181
00:11:11,666 --> 00:11:13,750
[HARUTO] Is putting
on weight a bad thing?

182
00:11:13,833 --> 00:11:15,916
[WITCH OF GLUTTONY]
Mm-hm.

183
00:11:16,000 --> 00:11:18,208
The last time I ate and
gained weight, I ended up

184
00:11:18,291 --> 00:11:20,916
getting dumped by my boyfriend.

185
00:11:21,000 --> 00:11:24,458
[MIREI] Joining clubs, study
groups, playing with friends.

186
00:11:24,541 --> 00:11:27,125
Falling in love.

187
00:11:27,208 --> 00:11:30,916
Being able to just enjoy
the moment. That's all.

188
00:11:31,000 --> 00:11:33,000
Like the other kids got to.

189
00:11:33,083 --> 00:11:36,375
That's the only thing
I've ever wanted.

190
00:11:36,458 --> 00:11:38,666
Involved? They're all guilty!

191
00:11:38,750 --> 00:11:40,666
Those spineless fools knew
what was happening,

192
00:11:40,750 --> 00:11:42,291
and pretended not
to see anything!

193
00:11:42,375 --> 00:11:43,833
They deserve it!

194
00:11:43,916 --> 00:11:46,250
[NENE]
Did you forget that?

195
00:11:46,333 --> 00:11:49,583
[YOSHITSUNE]
Pot. H-He died because of me.

196
00:11:49,666 --> 00:11:54,166
I will never forget that!
There's no way I ever could!

197
00:12:06,416 --> 00:12:08,833
[SUONO] It's not as if everyone
has to follow the same path

198
00:12:08,916 --> 00:12:10,416
in life as each other.

199
00:12:10,500 --> 00:12:12,750
But if you can understand
an inkling of the ideas

200
00:12:12,833 --> 00:12:15,875
I've been sharing,
then I'll be so glad.

201
00:12:15,958 --> 00:12:18,625
By learning about the
uniqueness of another person.

202
00:12:18,708 --> 00:12:21,875
By changing your point of
view just the slightest bit,

203
00:12:21,958 --> 00:12:23,666
your feelings towards
that person allow

204
00:12:23,750 --> 00:12:25,708
for a closer connection.

205
00:12:25,791 --> 00:12:28,208
Getting to know one another,
listening intently,

206
00:12:28,291 --> 00:12:32,833
without judgment, for their
inner voice to emerge and speak.

207
00:12:32,916 --> 00:12:34,250
[gasps]

208
00:12:34,333 --> 00:12:37,541
She'll be a top idol
for eternity! A shooting star

209
00:12:37,625 --> 00:12:40,000
loved by millions of
people across the nation!

210
00:12:40,083 --> 00:12:42,291
She doesn't fall in love,
or have to go to the bathroom!

211
00:12:42,375 --> 00:12:44,625
Misaki's a perfect idol!

212
00:12:46,750 --> 00:12:48,666
[MISAKI]
A perfect idol?

213
00:12:48,750 --> 00:12:51,958
I'm not sure anyone is
worthy of that title.

214
00:12:52,041 --> 00:12:57,416
Cheer up, Jane. It'll be okay.
You don't have to worry.

215
00:12:57,500 --> 00:13:00,625
[JANE] This is the part where
I draw you in close, Haruto.

216
00:13:03,250 --> 00:13:04,625
Listen to me, Jane.

217
00:13:04,708 --> 00:13:07,375
This dream must end, okay?

218
00:13:07,458 --> 00:13:11,500
Please! I know you can do it!

219
00:13:12,541 --> 00:13:18,750
We'll go, together! Come on.
Summon your courage, and rise!

220
00:13:18,833 --> 00:13:22,083
What does a make-believe world
like this have for you?

221
00:13:22,166 --> 00:13:25,250
Open your eyes,
and start walking, Jane.

222
00:13:25,333 --> 00:13:29,625
Don't give up, Jane.
I know you can do it, Jane!

223
00:13:29,708 --> 00:13:35,583
Jane! Jane! Jane! Jane! Jane!
Jane! Jane! Jane! Jane! Jane!

224
00:13:35,666 --> 00:13:39,333
Jane! Argh! I'm done!

225
00:13:39,416 --> 00:13:41,500
Well, I never really thought
of them as witches.

226
00:13:41,583 --> 00:13:44,666
They just seemed to have
their own issues to deal with.

227
00:13:44,750 --> 00:13:46,333
[LILY] There are many
witches in the world,

228
00:13:46,416 --> 00:13:48,916
but not even I knew which of
them had become key figures

229
00:13:49,000 --> 00:13:51,625
in our struggle against Eve.

230
00:13:51,708 --> 00:13:54,250
But the witches were the ones
who contacted you each time,

231
00:13:54,333 --> 00:13:55,791
not the other way around.

232
00:13:55,875 --> 00:13:58,708
That's how we discovered
who the linchpins were.

233
00:14:05,916 --> 00:14:07,083
But why did they search me out?

234
00:14:07,166 --> 00:14:08,458
Because you are you.

235
00:14:08,541 --> 00:14:10,708
That doesn't explain anything.

236
00:14:10,791 --> 00:14:12,791
[LILY] When the ten
linchpins have been removed,

237
00:14:12,875 --> 00:14:15,625
the door to Eve opens.

238
00:14:15,708 --> 00:14:17,666
Brother, come with
me to her door.

239
00:14:17,750 --> 00:14:19,750
[HARUTO] What'll we
do when we get there?

240
00:14:19,833 --> 00:14:21,958
I want you to stop
Eve from waking up.

241
00:14:22,041 --> 00:14:24,333
Stop her how?

242
00:14:24,416 --> 00:14:25,708
[LILY]
By killing her.

243
00:14:25,791 --> 00:14:29,083
Kill her? But why? Why don't
you just do it yourself?

244
00:14:29,166 --> 00:14:31,375
I mean, you're the one who
wants her dead, not me.

245
00:14:31,458 --> 00:14:33,000
Because. I can't do it.

246
00:14:33,083 --> 00:14:34,291
Why not?

247
00:14:34,375 --> 00:14:36,583
You saw it right?
The world coming to an end.

248
00:14:36,666 --> 00:14:38,625
All of mankind will be killed.

249
00:14:38,708 --> 00:14:40,625
You still haven't
answered my question!

250
00:14:40,708 --> 00:14:44,166
[EHYEH] Professor. You know
who the evil one is, correct?

251
00:14:44,250 --> 00:14:45,875
[KANZAKI]
Inside dreams, I do.

252
00:14:45,958 --> 00:14:48,666
I'd like to ask you to
help us stop him.

253
00:14:48,750 --> 00:14:50,750
He puts in jeopardy
all we strive for.

254
00:14:50,833 --> 00:14:54,083
Ten witches have already
awoken because of the evil one.

255
00:14:55,708 --> 00:14:57,625
Now. Open your eyes.

256
00:14:57,708 --> 00:14:58,875
[THE WITCH OF THUNDER gasps]

257
00:15:12,166 --> 00:15:14,625
I wish we'd met long ago.

258
00:15:22,208 --> 00:15:24,416
I have a new dream.
What that means,

259
00:15:24,500 --> 00:15:26,166
I'll have to learn.

260
00:15:27,625 --> 00:15:29,208
Thanks for your help.

261
00:15:38,458 --> 00:15:45,166
[KAYO] Thank you, Haruto.
You made me feel joyful.

262
00:15:45,250 --> 00:15:47,416
I've never been happier!

263
00:15:59,625 --> 00:16:03,458
I love you. I hope
you'll remember that.

264
00:16:08,125 --> 00:16:10,083
Keep me in your heart.

265
00:16:24,625 --> 00:16:27,208
[HARUTO]
Aah!

266
00:16:27,291 --> 00:16:29,541
[WITCH OF GLUTTONY]
Aah!

267
00:16:35,083 --> 00:16:36,500
Oh!

268
00:16:42,666 --> 00:16:46,958
Yes! It's good! And so fun!

269
00:16:59,666 --> 00:17:02,333
Right... Fate.

270
00:17:02,416 --> 00:17:06,458
[HARUTO] It's the one place you
can really be yourself. You see?

271
00:17:06,541 --> 00:17:08,000
[MIREI]
Yes.

272
00:17:08,083 --> 00:17:12,708
In the long run, this is the
only path I have, isn't it?

273
00:17:16,875 --> 00:17:19,875
[YUKI] That's right, Mirei.
Gliding gracefully across

274
00:17:19,958 --> 00:17:23,000
the ice is where you
shine your brightest.

275
00:17:23,083 --> 00:17:26,416
Keep on skating. You were
meant to be a star.

276
00:17:26,500 --> 00:17:27,875
You were born to it.

277
00:17:27,958 --> 00:17:29,708
[LILY]
That's destiny.

278
00:17:36,208 --> 00:17:40,041
[inaudible]

279
00:17:40,125 --> 00:17:41,458
[HARUTO chuckles]

280
00:17:44,666 --> 00:17:46,458
[HARUTO]
It's gonna be all right.

281
00:17:46,541 --> 00:17:49,958
Knowing you, you're strong
enough to bounce back.

282
00:17:50,041 --> 00:17:53,583
Then, that means...
I must still be alive!

283
00:17:53,666 --> 00:17:55,708
[HARUTO]
Mm-hm.

284
00:17:55,791 --> 00:17:58,875
Oh, good. That means I
can get out of here!

285
00:17:58,958 --> 00:18:01,625
That's all up to you,
from this point.

286
00:18:01,708 --> 00:18:04,250
Are you prepared to face
the harshness of reality?

287
00:18:04,333 --> 00:18:07,000
That's a choice you'll
have to make for yourself.

288
00:18:07,083 --> 00:18:08,583
I am ready.

289
00:18:11,333 --> 00:18:15,750
Thanks, Haruto... and farewell.

290
00:18:24,666 --> 00:18:28,125
[SUONO] I'm glad! Thankful I
got the chance to meet you!

291
00:18:30,541 --> 00:18:32,083
[HARUTO]
Hm!

292
00:18:32,166 --> 00:18:34,291
[SUONO]
I'll see you around!

293
00:18:36,666 --> 00:18:37,958
[HARUTO]
Huh?

294
00:18:47,916 --> 00:18:50,666
Now then, the spell is about
to be broken, my lady.

295
00:18:50,750 --> 00:18:52,208
Take care, now.

296
00:19:01,416 --> 00:19:03,958
[JANE] He was willing
to give me a chance.

297
00:19:04,041 --> 00:19:07,000
Yeah? Does that mean I can
see you again on the outside?

298
00:19:07,083 --> 00:19:09,750
[JANE] What? Would you be
interested in being my friend?

299
00:19:09,833 --> 00:19:11,333
[KANZAKI]
Of course.

300
00:19:13,541 --> 00:19:15,375
Tin man.

301
00:19:23,666 --> 00:19:27,250
The interference of the evil one
has angered our goddess, Eve.

302
00:19:27,333 --> 00:19:29,166
Why did he awaken the maidens?

303
00:19:29,250 --> 00:19:32,250
What right did he have to
tamper with their emotions?

304
00:19:32,333 --> 00:19:36,250
Now Eve is trying to wake up,
stirred by her displeasure.

305
00:19:36,333 --> 00:19:38,541
Then, Eve is waking
up out of anger?

306
00:19:38,625 --> 00:19:41,375
Will she try to save mankind
after she lets off some steam?

307
00:19:41,458 --> 00:19:44,708
We pray for her to wake,
not out of anger, but instead,

308
00:19:44,791 --> 00:19:47,250
out of pure love
for her children.

309
00:19:47,333 --> 00:19:48,916
"Love" is another
ambiguous word,

310
00:19:49,000 --> 00:19:51,250
when held in the
context you're using.

311
00:19:51,333 --> 00:19:53,208
If it is love that
reawakens our goddess,

312
00:19:53,291 --> 00:19:55,000
she'd forgive the world
for what was learned

313
00:19:55,083 --> 00:19:56,583
from the Tree of Knowledge.

314
00:19:56,666 --> 00:19:59,291
That's the only way humanity can
hope to escape the punishment

315
00:19:59,375 --> 00:20:01,541
God set aside for us.

316
00:20:01,625 --> 00:20:04,416
[KANZAKI] All right.
So, if Eve is woken out of love,

317
00:20:04,500 --> 00:20:06,625
and comes to save us,
her children,

318
00:20:06,708 --> 00:20:08,958
then what kind of
world will await us?

319
00:20:09,041 --> 00:20:12,000
[EHYEH] The whole world would
become Sleeping Beautys.

320
00:20:20,250 --> 00:20:21,833
I don't think I
fully understand,

321
00:20:21,916 --> 00:20:24,375
but it sounds depressing.

322
00:20:34,125 --> 00:20:35,666
Don't believe a thing they say.

323
00:20:35,750 --> 00:20:37,000
[KANZAKI gasps]

324
00:20:39,708 --> 00:20:41,125
[KANZAKI]
Who are you?

325
00:20:41,208 --> 00:20:43,583
[AKITO] Someone who despises
the Thorn Cross Association.

326
00:20:43,666 --> 00:20:45,291
That's all that counts.

327
00:20:45,375 --> 00:20:47,166
Do you know something
I should know?

328
00:20:47,250 --> 00:20:49,083
Do I look like I do?

329
00:20:49,166 --> 00:20:51,708
If not, then why did you
bother talking to me?

330
00:20:51,791 --> 00:20:53,875
Take it easy, I'm just
trying to warn you.

331
00:20:53,958 --> 00:20:56,083
You don't want to fall for the
line of bull those fools are

332
00:20:56,166 --> 00:20:57,583
trying to sell.

333
00:20:57,666 --> 00:21:00,458
You're being very evasive.
What is it that you're hiding?

334
00:21:00,541 --> 00:21:04,208
Not a thing. I just said I
hated those guys, didn't I?

335
00:21:04,291 --> 00:21:07,583
Anyway, I'd steer clear of them
from now on, if I were you.

336
00:21:07,666 --> 00:21:10,208
You want to enjoy
a long life, right?

337
00:21:12,666 --> 00:21:13,875
[KANZAKI gasps]

338
00:21:15,916 --> 00:21:17,791
That kid's a weirdo.

339
00:21:19,166 --> 00:21:21,625
[phone rings]

340
00:21:21,708 --> 00:21:25,250
[YUKO] Yes? Oh, Professor!
It's been a long time.

341
00:21:25,333 --> 00:21:26,750
[KANZAKI]
It's been a while.

342
00:21:26,833 --> 00:21:28,708
There's something I
wanted to ask you.

343
00:21:28,791 --> 00:21:31,833
[YUKO] Something to
ask me? What is it?

344
00:21:31,916 --> 00:21:34,416
[KANZAKI] It's about Haruto.
And not just you.

345
00:21:34,500 --> 00:21:37,166
I was hoping to speak with
all the other witches as well.

346
00:21:37,250 --> 00:21:39,083
[YUKO]
About Haruto?

347
00:21:39,166 --> 00:21:41,750
Then there's a lot that we
would like to share with you,

348
00:21:41,833 --> 00:21:43,333
now that you mention it.

349
00:21:43,416 --> 00:21:45,875
[KANZAKI]
Huh? Did you say "We"?

350
00:21:45,958 --> 00:21:48,916
[YUKO]
Yes, all of the former witches.

351
00:21:55,833 --> 00:21:57,125
[HARUTO]
If I open this,

352
00:21:57,208 --> 00:21:59,958
then I'll be at the door
that leads me to Eve, right?

353
00:22:00,041 --> 00:22:01,291
[LILY]
Yes.

354
00:22:01,375 --> 00:22:04,625
[HARUTO] Well okay.
I guess I have no choice.

355
00:22:10,250 --> 00:22:13,291
[EVE chuckels]

356
00:22:13,375 --> 00:22:18,333
♪


357
00:23:46,291 --> 00:23:48,750
[LILY] The witch's singing
voice rings out.

358
00:23:48,833 --> 00:23:52,291
Turn your ears towards her,
and listen to her feelings!

359
00:23:52,375 --> 00:23:54,541
[EGOS]
Listen up, baa!

360
00:23:54,625 --> 00:23:57,916
[LILY] Next time's dream is:
"The Witch Wars."

